      "citation_id": "[CITATION_7]",
      "span_text": "Val158Met). Studies of the South African Caucasian OCD population have identified this polymorphism as a risk factor for both the disorder and certain symptom dimensions within OCD. The low activity 158Met allele was found to be correlated with more severe symptomatology associated with hoarding in male Afrikaner OCD patients and in a subsequent study, a cluster of symptoms in South African Caucasian OCD patients that included \"symmetry and ordering\". The sexual dimorphism detected with COMT 158Met and the hoarding symptom dimension of OCD by Lochner et al. has also been observed with regards to this polymorphism and susceptibility to the disorder."
